The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, June 13, 2004 				 BoI plans to raise Rs 100 cr
																								Mumbai, June 12 (PTI): The Bank of India (BoI) board today approved a proposal to raise Rs 100 crore capital through a public issue to augment its resources. 																								The board has given its approval for an enabling resolution to raise Rs 100 crore. However, there is no immediate plans for the second public offering, BoI chairman and managing director M. Venugopal said here.																								The banks current capital adequacy ratio was pegged at around 13 per cent, he said. We will tap the market at an appropriate time, he added.																								The bank would also seek shareholders approval for the resolution.																								BoI had made its first public issue in 1997 to raise Rs 150 crore. 
